# Cursor rules ↔ Claude `CLAUDE.md` parity

This repo maintains two instruction surfaces for AI assistants:

| Surface | Location |
|--------|----------|
| **Cursor** | [`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`](.cursor/rules/) |
| **Claude** (project context) | [`CLAUDE.md`](../CLAUDE.md) at the repo root |

**When you create, update, or remove project-wide AI guidance in one place, apply the same change to the other** so instructions stay consistent. If something is intentionally specific to one tool, state that in **both** places in a one-line note so neither assistant assumes parity where there is none.

Rules that only exist under `.cursor/rules/` (for example `scratch-local-brainstorm.mdc`) should still have a short mirror in **`CLAUDE.md`** when they describe repo-wide conventions.

**End-user `tray` CLI skills** (for people *using* the binary, not hacking the repo) live in [`skills/`](../skills/README.md). Maintainer-facing bullets also point there from [`cli-architecture.mdc`](cli-architecture.mdc) and [`CLAUDE.md`](../CLAUDE.md); the canonical file is [`skills/tray-cli/SKILL.md`](../skills/tray-cli/SKILL.md).
